story.p:
There was once upon a time a woman named Pascadozzia. As she was standing one day at a window, which looked into the garden of an ogress,
she saw a beautiful bed of parsley, for which she took such a longing that she was on the point of fainting away; 
and being unable to resist her desire, she watched until the ogress went out, and then plucked a handful of it.
